headline: Britain rejects call to regulate cryptoassets as a form of gambling
lead: Treating cryptoassets as a form of gambling would put Britain at odds with global and European Union regulators and fail to mitigate risks from the sector, Britain?s Financial Services Minister Andrew Griffith said on Thursday.

headline: No Cognitive Benefit From Meditation, Learning a Language?
lead: Meditation and foreign language training does not boost cognitive function in cognitively healthy older adults, a new study suggests.

headline: State College man sentenced to jail for crash that killed Penn State student
lead: A State College man on Thursday pleaded guilty to homicide by vehicle and was sentenced to 16 to 32 months in prison for an August 2021 crash that killed a Penn State student.

headline: Ethiopia war ?the most deadly? as world sees record high battle-related deaths in 2022 since 1984
lead: A new report by the non-profit Peace Research Institute Oslo (PRIO) revealed that with more than 100,000 fatalities, the war in Ethiopia, which was third deadliest in 2021, became the most deadly conflict in the world in 2022, as the year records highest battle-related deaths from state-based conflicts than in any year since 1984.

headline: A house where you could charge up your Tesla via the 16th-century water mill
lead: Want to make your own power but don't want solar panels on the roof? There's an answer at Mullybrook Mill in Devon, a house with plenty of history, machinery and potential to become a restoration project that could lead to self-sufficiency.

headline: US, Japan, South Korea to hold summit in August: Seoul
lead: South Korean, US and Japanese leaders will meet in August in America, Seoul?s presidential office said Thursday, as the three nations increase military cooperation to counter North Korea?s growing nuclear threats.

headline: Tornado Causes Major Damage To Pfizer Facility In NC, Scorching Heat, Floods Hit Other States
lead: A tornado heavily damaged a major Pfizer pharmaceutical plant in North Carolina on Wednesday, while torrential rain flooded communities in Kentucky and an area from California to South Florida endured more scorching heat.

headline: U.S. says had "candid" exchange with EU on meeting aluminum deal deadline
lead: U.S. Trade Representative Katherine Tai had a "direct and candid exchange" with EU trade chief Valdis Dombrovskis on Thursday about the work required to meet an October deadline to deliver an aluminum and steel deal, according to her office.

headline: Prices still rising while farmers paid less
lead: It is good news that inflation has finally dipped by more than forecast, although at 7.9% it remains damaging and far above the Bank of England's 2% target rate.

headline: Supermarkets not responsible for food price inflation as profits fall
lead: Supermarkets are not the cause of food price inflation in the UK with profits down by more than 40%, a new Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) report has said.

headline: How the COVID-19 pandemic altered antibiotic prescribing for common bacterial infections
lead: In a study posted to the medRxiv* preprint server, investigators evaluated the impact of the coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) pandemic on the use of antibiotics in primary care for common infections.

headline: Massive blasts at Russian depot in Crimea force thousands to flee
lead: A series of explosions roared through a Russian ammunition storage facility in occupied Crimea on Wednesday, forcing thousands of residents of nearby areas to flee and prompting leaders there to redirect traffic away from a local highway.

headline: Measles: how declining vaccination levels in London are threatening herd immunity
lead: Projections from the UKHSA suggest London could see a measles outbreak totalling 40,000 to 160,000 cases at current vaccination levels.
